\"'quiz-submitted'\">{{ 'artemisApp.courseOverview.exerciseList.userSubmittedShort' | translate }}</span>\n             </div>\n-            <span *ngSwitchCase=\"'initialized'\">\n-                <jhi-updating-result class=\"mr-2\" [exercise]=\"exercise\" [participation]=\"studentParticipation\" [showGradedBadge]=\"true\"></jhi-updating-result>\n-            </span>\n-            <span *ngSwitchCase=\"'inactive'\">\n-                <jhi-updating-result class=\"mr-2\" [exercise]=\"exercise\" [participation]=\"studentParticipation\" [showGradedBadge]=\"true\"></jhi-updating-result>\n-            </span>\n-            <span *ngSwitchCase=\"'quiz-finished'\">\n-                <jhi-updating-result class=\"mr-2\" [exercise]=\"exercise\" [participation]=\"studentParticipation\" [showGradedBadge]=\"true\"></jhi-updating-result>\n-            </span>\n-            <span *ngSwitchCase=\"'exercise-submitted'\">\n-                <jhi-updating-result class=\"mr-2\" [exercise]=\"exercise\" [participation]=\"studentParticipation\" [showGradedBadge]=\"true\"></jhi-updating-result>\n-            </span>\n+            <div class=\"my-2\">\n+                <span *ngSwitchCase=\"'initialized'\">", "originalCommit": "2ca46556519afb598e2f67ce53dfd8f5857d0b73", "replyToReviewId": null, "replies": [{"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM2MzgyODg5NQ==", "url": "https://github.com/ls1intum/Artemis/pull/1174#discussion_r363828895", "bodyText": "Oh, good catch. Weird code duplication indeed. Will refactor it.", "author": "madwau", "createdAt": "2020-01-07T16:19:16Z", "replyToReviewId": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM2Mzc0MjY4MQ=="}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM2MzgzMjczNQ==", "url": "https://github.com/ls1intum/Artemis/pull/1174#discussion_r363832735", "bodyText": "Done.", "author": "madwau", "createdAt": "2020-01-07T16:26:51Z", "replyToReviewId": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM2Mzc0MjY4MQ=="}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM2NDExNzIyNg==", "url": "https://github.com/ls1intum/Artemis/pull/1174#discussion_r364117226", "bodyText": "Are you sure that you did not change the logic here? And did you test that exactly these cases work as before? I am not sure if you can combine ngSwitch and ngIf like that.", "author": "krusche", "createdAt": "2020-01-08T08:46:15Z", "replyToReviewId": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM2Mzc0MjY4MQ=="}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM2NTUyNjQxNw==", "url": "https://github.com/ls1intum/Artemis/pull/1174#discussion_r365526417", "bodyText": "I tested that for all these cases ['initialized', 'inactive', 'quiz-finished', 'exercise-submitted'] the updating result component is rendered and I picked a couple of other cases not in that list and verified that the updating result component is not rendered for them.\nCombining ngSwitch and ngIf should not be an issue in this case since the ngIf stands on its own and does not depend on the switch context. It explicitly references exercise.participationStatus as compared to the implicit reference that happens in the case of the ngSwitchCase statements.\nIn fact, this construct already exists just below where ng-container uses ngIf within the ngSwitch scope.", "author": "madwau", "createdAt": "2020-01-11T15:12:18Z", "replyToReviewId": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM2Mzc0MjY4MQ=="}], "type": "inlineReview"}, {"oid": "cfa355ab5dbedbcd3d0885ce119d02c9ca91e617", "url": "https://github.com/ls1intum/Artemis/commit/cfa355ab5dbedbcd3d0885ce119d02c9ca91e617", "message": "Merge branch 'develop' into bugfix/exercises/overlapping-elements", "committedDate": "2020-01-07T16:20:24Z", "type": "commit"}, {"oid": "9f0b662236768e83080e80ac3e7078dd2b3941b7", "url": "https://github.com/ls1intum/Artemis/commit/9f0b662236768e83080e80ac3e7078dd2b3941b7", "message": "Refactor", "committedDate": "2020-01-07T16:26:35Z", "type": "commit"}, {"oid": "33a968936a39a659db12f077f9f1ec1a0614b1a7", "url": "https://github.com/ls1intum/